# Operator-specific AI memory (never commit)
# Both paths are gitignored:
# - .claude/ was the original location; left ignored to defend against any
#   tool that auto-creates files there.
# - private/ is the active location for operator-private memory (local.md
#   etc.) since 2026-04-26 — Cowork's sandbox blocks AI Write/Edit on
#   `.claude/`, so the file moved here to keep AI-driven IM updates
#   working without a chat-paste roundtrip.
.claude/
private/

# Stray scratch files
CLAUDE.md.tmp
*.tmp
pytest-cache-files-*

# v0.4 phone app (MAUI Blazor) — source tracked under /phone/, build
# artifacts (bin/, obj/, .vs/, NuGet packages, Android APK staging,
# iOS DerivedData) are not. The /phone/ folder itself stays in the
# repo so contributors can build the app; only its compile outputs
# are ignored.
/phone/**/bin/
/phone/**/obj/
/phone/**/.vs/
/phone/**/packages/
/phone/**/Properties/launchSettings.json
/phone/**/AppPackages/
/phone/**/Resources/Raw/.gitkeep
/phone/**/*.user
/phone/**/*.suo

# Phone-app credential ceremony artifacts. Each operator deploying
# Recto runs their own Apple Developer Program + Firebase Console
# ceremony per dev-tools/README.md; the resulting credential files are
# operator-specific and never get checked in. Forkers regenerate them
# for their own bundle ID + Firebase project. Public Recto repo carries
# only the wire-up that READS these files; the values stay on the
# operator's machine.
/phone/**/dev-tools/.fcm-service-account.json
/phone/**/dev-tools/.apns-auth-key.p8
/phone/**/dev-tools/.credentials.md
/phone/**/google-services.json
# Catch-alls so future credential files of these shapes are protected
# even if the directory layout changes:
/phone/**/*-firebase-adminsdk-*.json
/phone/**/*.p8
/phone/**/AuthKey_*.p8
/phone/**/GoogleService-Info.plist
